    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-09T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-09T03:00:00-05:00" n="614"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5477: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-09T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 9, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 9—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>921. Your 242, August 6, 3 p.m. Subject matter my 904, August 6, 10 a.m., given
                    to colleagues this morning. It was suggested that we would find it difficult to
                    refuse to consider the question if the Chinese were seriously to propose
                    neutralization of Peiping but all agreed that it would be dangerous to consider
                    the question without knowing more of the plans of both sides.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
